Channel5Plus1.uk.title: Supermarket Own Brands: The Big Taste Test

Channel5Plus1.uk.title: New: Dogs Behaving (Very) Badly

Channel5Plus1.uk.title: New: The Good Ship Murder

Channel5Plus1.uk.title: PlayOJO Live Casino Show

Channel5Plus1.uk.title: Save Money on Your Supermarket Shop

E4Plus1.uk.title: Hollyoaks
E4Plus1.uk.description: Old friends return to lift Donny's spirits. And it's a race against time as a revenge plot closes in on one resident.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Once Upon a Time in Springfield: Krusty gets a beautiful new co-star (guest voice Anne Hathaway). Mr Burns withdraws the staff's free doughnuts at the nuclear power plant. (S21 Ep10/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Inside the World's Most...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Luxurious Cruises: A look behind the scenes aboard some of the world's most opulent cruise ships, where suites cost up to 8k a night and pets are as pampered as their people. (S1 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Goggleboxers watch The Gentlemen, Casualty, Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?, Crufts, Queens, and Martin Compston's Norwegian Fling. (S23 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Goggleboxers watch The Great Celebrity Bake Off for SU2C, Hunted, One Day, Anton & Giovanni's Adventures in Spain, Married at First Sight Australia and more. (S23 Ep6)

Film4.uk.title: Fighting with my Family...
Film4.uk.description: ...Interview Special: Florence Pugh, Jack Lowden, Nick Frost and director Stephen Merchant discuss making the comedy-drama that's based on a real-life family of wrestlers from Norwich.

Film4.uk.title: The Bravados
Film4.uk.description: (1958) Brooding western starring Joan Collins and Gregory Peck. A man hunts down the four escaped prisoners who he believes are responsible for the murder of his wife.

Film4.uk.description: (1950) Western. James Stewart stars as sharpshooter Lin McAdam, who wins a Winchester rifle. But a murderous rival steals his prize, so McAdam sets out on an epic journey in pursuit.

Film4.uk.title: Guadalcanal Diary
Film4.uk.description: (1943) Second World War action drama following two US marines as they make advances into the Solomon Islands to drive back the Japanese forces. Starring Preston Foster and Lloyd Nolan.

Film4.uk.title: Jumanji: The Next Level
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Adventure comedy sequel with Dwayne Johnson, Jack Black, Kevin Hart and Karen Gillan. The old school pals enter the Jumanji video game again to save their friend.

Film4.uk.title: The Contractor
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Action thriller with Chris Pine. An ex-soldier takes on private work to feed his family, but finds himself in dire straits (danger; not the band). With Kiefer Sutherland.

Film4.uk.title: Commando
Film4.uk.description: (1985) Thriller starring Arnold Schwarzenegger. To free his kidnapped daughter, an ex US commando must agree to assassinate a South American president. But he's not as pliant as he seems...

Film4.uk.title: Les Misrables
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Ladj Ly's oscar-nominated drama, loosely based on his childhood and set in the struggling Parisian suburbs of Montfermeil during the 2018 riots. In French/subs.

GBNews.uk.title: Alex Armstrong Tonight
GBNews.uk.description: Join Alex for two hours of lively debate and news making interviews. Top guests tackle the big issues of the day with Alex's fresh take on every story.

GBNews.uk.title: Alex Armstrong Tonight Late Edition
GBNews.uk.description: Tomorrow's news, tonight. All the major stories making the front pages and full coverage of all the breaking news at home and abroad with Alex Armstrong.

GBNews.uk.title: The Late Show Live
GBNews.uk.description: Live from Washington DC, Bev Turner and Ben Leo bring you the latest from the US and what it means for Britain.

GBNews.uk.title: The Camilla Tominey Show Highlights
GBNews.uk.description: Highlights from this morning. Join Camilla Tominey for a Sunday morning politics show with personality, live from Westminster.

GBNews.uk.title: Alex Armstrong Tonight
GBNews.uk.description: Join Alex for two hours of lively debate and news making interviews. Top guests tackle the big issues of the day with Alex's fresh take on every story.

GBNews.uk.title: Alex Armstrong Tonight Late Edition
GBNews.uk.description: Tomorrow's news, tonight. All the major stories making the front pages and full coverage of all the breaking news at home and abroad with Alex Armstrong.

GBNews.uk.title: Breakfast with Eamonn and Ellie
GBNews.uk.description: Join Eamonn Holmes & Ellie Costello to start your day across the United Kingdom. This is your breakfast show. Join the conversation about what is happening in our nation and the world.

GBNews.uk.title: Britain's Newsroom
GBNews.uk.description: Andrew and Miriam present Monday to Thursday mornings. When the news happens, it happens here. GB News brings you the biggest stories and the answers you need from across the UK.

GBNews.uk.title: Good Afternoon Britain
GBNews.uk.description: Tackling the big stories from all angles and perspectives. Weekdays from midday, Tom Harwood and Nana Akua bring you the most compelling stories from across the United Kingdom.

GBNews.uk.title: Martin Daubney
GBNews.uk.description: Join Martin for an up-to-the-minute take on the day's events delivered in his own unique and lively style.

GBNews.uk.title: Dewbs & Co
GBNews.uk.description: Plain-speaking, straight-talking - Michelle delivers her individual take on the day's news.
